silero_vad.bin — attribution and license
=========================================

This file (silero_vad.bin) contains the Silero VAD (v6, 16 kHz) neural-network
weights, converted into dasLLAMA's container format by
modules/dasLLAMA/harness/convert_silero_vad.py from the official
`silero_vad_16k_op15.onnx` initializers shipped in the MIT-licensed `silero-vad`
Python package (version 6.2.1).

  Source project : Silero VAD — https://github.com/snakers4/silero-vad
  Upstream author: Silero Team <hello@silero.ai>
  Model version  : v6, 16 kHz mono
  License        : MIT (reproduced in full below, per its terms)

The weights are redistributed unmodified in numerical content (only repackaged
into a flat binary); the dasLLAMA reimplementation in dasllama_vad.das reproduces
the official ONNX model's per-frame output bit-faithfully (max|Δ| < 1e-5 vs
onnxruntime). No affiliation with or endorsement by the Silero Team is implied.

